{"id": "duc04-testb-26:0#1", "contents": "The commission's decision to remove de Klerk's name from the report was met with disappointment from Tutu, who expressed that it \"upsets me deeply.\" However, he emphasized that the commission must respect the courts and de Klerk's rights under the constitution. Tutu noted that the commission had been \"scrupulously fair\" to de Klerk and rejected the contention that they had been engaged in a vendetta against him. He added that the name would eventually appear in the report after the legal challenge had been resolved."}
